»CL0:    Hard Bounced Diskmag Critisism
»CL1:--------------------------------------

Ideas have faded into »CL0:oblivion»CL1:.  There
aren't any new and innovative subjects
left  which haven't been written about
in   the   past.   Almost  every  »CL0:Very
Important  Scener»CL1: has been interviewed
already.    Report's   discribing  the
state  of  a  scene country or a group
have  all been done before.  There are








only  a  handfull of interesting scene
»CL0:parties»CL1:  left  to  write  fragile  and
non-quality  party reports about.  The
»CL0:Polish»CL1:   connection   is  one  hundred
percent debated; That's for sure!  The
»CL6:Eurochart»CL4:s»CL1: and »CL6:Showtime»CL1: survive trough
headhunting  for votes.  (It's a laugh
to   see   »CL2:Darkhawk»CL1:  asking  virtually
everybody  at  »CL0:#amigascne»CL1:  to vote the
last few weeks before the release of a
new »CL6:Eurochart»CL4:s»CL1: issue.) »CL2:RokDaZoNe»CL1:, »CL2:Mop»CL1:,
»CL2:Astro  Wolfman»CL1:  & »CL2: Mount»CL1:, »CL2:Lord Helmet»CL1:,
»CL2:Macno»CL1:, »CL2:Cybersonik»CL1:,»CL2: Colorbird»CL1:,»CL2: Diesel 8»CL1:
and alot more editors quit writing and
are  living their own lives.  And what
about  those  diskmags  we  can't read
because  they  are  »CL0:Polish»CL1: only ?  All
writing  styles  have  been  explored,
nothing  new  to  gain  there  either.
»CL0:Comebacks»CL1:  or a small»CL0: re-appearence»CL1: by
old writers have already been made and
done.   These  day's most articles are
based  on  the personal »CL0:opinion»CL1: of the
writer,  how  »CL0:egoistic»CL1:,  how »CL0: selfish»CL1:.
Where   is   the  balanced  stream  of
»CL0:quality»CL1:  and  »CL0:interesting»CL1:  articles we
knew in earlier times when for example
»CL6:Upstream»CL1:,»CL6:  Rom»CL1:, »CL6: Raw»CL1: and »CL6:Seenpoint»CL1: got
released  ?  There is nothing new left
to  explore  with  writing.   There is
nothing      left     than     selfish
»CL0:ego-stimulation»CL1:,   »CL0: mud-trowing»CL1:    and
provocative  »CL0: spandimerda»CL1:!   We  don't
need such articles with a goal to lift
some »CL0: reaction»CL1:.   And  then  those »CL0:old»CL1:
writer's  who  haven't  been following
the  scene  the last few »CL0:years»CL1: but are
still  trying to write articles.  They
can't  do anything else than cover old
topic's,  write  about things from the
»CL0:past»CL1:   or   write  those »CL0: mud-trowing»CL1:,
selfish »CL0:   spandimerda»CL1:!    You   know,
nothing  lasts forever, some things we
will never understand, we just need to
»CL0:accept»CL1:  the  situation  of  the  Amiga
scene journalism anno domini 2001 !!!

