»CL0:          MPEG Amiga Demos..
»CL1:--------------------------------------

Not  so  long ago, about a month after
»CL6:Mekka-Symposium  2001 »CL1: some sceners at
»CL0:#amigascne»CL1:  including  me  started  to
discuss a nice »CL0:www »CL1:site which has alot
of  Amiga Demo's online..  Nothing»CL0: new»CL1:
so  far,  unless you are a PC user now
and  still  want  to  see  some  Amiga
demo's..   No,  don't  use »CL0:WINUAE»CL1:, THE
amiga »CL0: emulator»CL1:  on  PC,  but download
some   nice  amiga  demo's  from  this
fabulous                      website:
»CL0:http://omr.planet-d.net/amidemos»CL1:.  All
the  demos  featured online are »CL0:mpeg's»CL1:
(in»CL0: divX»CL1: format) , a very nice service
to  see  some  older  and new demo's..
Some   demos   from  »CL6: ms2k1  »CL1:are  even
online..   Ofcourse you need to have a
»CL0:fast»CL1:  connection because a simple demo
is  already  around »CL0:20mb»CL1: to download..
Yes,  the  PC  scene  should be really
»CL0:scared»CL1:   now!!   A  sudden  change  of
cultures is at hand!!

